  "description": "Alongside a demo of <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/search/quick?game=Night+Shift\">Night Shift</a>, four complete unreleased games feature on this cassette. <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/search/quick?company=Atlantis\">Atlantis</a> founder <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/developer/sheet/view/developerId,651284/\">Graham Shaw</a> offers Hunter, a <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/search/quick?game=Duck+Hunt\">Duck Hunt</a> meets <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/game/operation-wolf\">Operation Wolf</a> fusion, in which shooting animals within the time limit, shooting bombs before they hit the ground, and shooting the gamekeeper before he shoots you, are the tasks.<br><br>Confused is an arcade puzzler in which the aim is to clear 13 screens of bombs, by walking to each bomb using a network of vertical teleports and on-off platforms.<br><br>Cult Spec-Chum <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/developer/sheet/view/developerId,199004/\">Andrey Remic</a> is behind the other two games. A Shadow on Glass in an interactive fiction game with graphics, while Space Worm is played out on a large grid, with the bulk of the game being short action sequences of your worm shooting everything, plus some squares in which bonus lives can be won.",
